FEATURES_AND_BENEFITS_6: Thin with high-tactile sensitivity

FEATURES_AND_BENEFITS_9: Unique formulation achieved with Low Derma Technology provides stronger durability than the traditionally manufactured nitrile glove material
FEATURES_AND_BENEFITS_10: Features a textured external surface and a chlorinated internal surface
FEATURES_AND_BENEFITS_11: Ambidextrous, standard-length, beaded-cuff design for convenience and comfort

FEATURES_AND_BENEFITS_13: Compatible for specialty, non-hospital applications such as safe food handling (non-toxic, powder-free) and by tattoo artists (masks stain)
FEATURES_AND_BENEFITS_14: Low-derma design manufactured without the use of accelerator chemicals to help protect users from nonallergic reactions to the numerous irritants from both glove and non-glove associated sources

FEATURES_AND_BENEFITS_3: For cleansing, irrigating, moistening, and debriding to remove wound debris from acute and chronic dermal lesions
FEATURES_AND_BENEFITS_4: Ideal for partial or full thickness wounds such as 1st and 2nd degree burns, stage I-IV pressure ulcers, diabetic ulcers, stasis ulcers, abrasions and minor skin irritations, post-surgical wounds, grafted and donor sites, in addition to moistening and lubricating absorbent wound dressings
FEATURES_AND_BENEFITS_5: Provides clinicians with a new alternative to commercial cleansers and solutions that may inhibit wound closure
FEATURES_AND_BENEFITS_6: Provide clinicians with an ideal solution for proper wound bed preparation
FEATURES_AND_BENEFITS_7: Non-cytotoxic, non-irritating, and won’t harm healthy tissue
FEATURES_AND_BENEFITS_8: Contains no steroids or antibiotics
FEATURES_AND_BENEFITS_9: Contains no alcohol or iodine
FEATURES_AND_BENEFITS_10: Convenient, ready-to-use formula requires no mixing or diluting and provided with a septum-capped bottle for easy application
FEATURES_AND_BENEFITS_11: Supports wound odor reduction
FEATURES_AND_BENEFITS_12: Environmentally friendly – no special disposal required
FEATURES_AND_BENEFITS_13: Safe solution –no known drug/treatment interactions with additional testing demonstrating no oral toxicity or genotoxicity
FEATURES_AND_BENEFITS_14: Features a long shelf life averaging up to 24 months
FEATURES_AND_BENEFITS_15: Hypochlorous acid (HOCl) used in the Puracyn®Plus technology is produced by an electrochemical process that generates a pH-balanced solution comprised of hypochlorous acid and its sodium salt, hypochlorite
FEATURES_AND_BENEFITS_16: Featured hypochlorous acid, a known antimicrobial, serves as a preservative to inhibit the growth of a broad range of microorganisms including staphylococcal species
FEATURES_AND_BENEFITS_17: Not made with natural rubber latex
